 moment, it can be abandoned. A body is not separate from the spaces it inhabits. They exist together, in a mutual state of interrelation and instability. Quarry relays a year in the life of a body in transition as it changes with other bodies; human, animal, and mineral. It examines queer social spaces and contested natural spaces, asking how they affect each other. Using evocative metaphor and refreshing language, these poems make bodily experience new. Tanis Franco eschews traditional narratives of the queer and transgender body, bringing nuanced ideas to an ongoing literary and philosophical conversation. Their strong sense of location and landscape is interwoven with sensual language and impeccable craft, creating a unique and distinctive voice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBody imagevPoetry. 0aFamiliesvFiction. 0aFathersvFiction. 0aGender identityvPoetry. 0aGender nonconformityvPoetry. 0aQuarries and quarryingvPoetry. 7aPOETRY / LGBT.2bisacsh  aDead Horse Bay.  aFire Island.  aGenderqueer poetry.  aLGBT Poetry.  aLGBTQ Night Life.  aMontreal.  aNew York City.  aQuebec.  aQueer Bars.  aQueer Poetry.  aTop Surgery.  aTrans Poetry.  aTransition.  aexperimental poetry.  ageology.  aquarries.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552389829?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552389829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552389829/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles